write a story. It will be garbage, the first story always is. Read over it, change inconsistencies. Then post it here, get feedback.
Write another.
Rinse and repeat.

If you specifically ask for opinions, i'm sure you'll get loads. Just don't despair if they seem negative but detailed. Ignore negative ones like "major things suck" unless they care to explain their opinion. Finally, get a meta look at this place through the stories. only by writing a green in adhg did i realize that the loud minority there is just too shy to approach women at all and needs the femdom to be able to self insert in to the protagonist because they otherwise wouldn't even talk to women and females taking charge is the only way they'd ever get any tail irl.

The silent majority seems to be fine with any femdom though, be it gentle or full blown my obsession levels of rapey.
Finding the meta of what people are looking for here will allow you to expect their reaction to what you're writing which can help with criticism.

Overall, writing is a craft. You'll have to learn it.
